.SH CONFIGURATION FILE
.sp
Tizonia ships with a configuration file template. See below for the system
locations where this template is usually installed. On first use, Tizonia
copies this file into the user\(aqs local configuration directory, usually in one
of these locations:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
\fB$HOME/.config/tizonia/tizonia.conf\fP (Debian and AUR installations)
.IP \(bu 2
\fB$HOME/snap/tizonia/current/.config/tizonia/tizonia.conf\fP (Snap installation)
.UNINDENT
.sp
Customization of this file by the user is typically required, e.g. to add
credentials for the subscribed streaming services. Note that Tizonia only reads
this file, never writes to it.
.sp
\fBWARNING:\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
When user names and passwords are stored in your local
\fBtizonia.conf\fP, please ensure that this file has the correct
file system permissions to prevent other users from accessing your
credentials.
.sp
E.g.: \fB$ chmod og\-rwx $HOME/.config/tizonia/tizonia.conf\fP
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Use \fBtizonia \-\-help config\fP for a reminder of the location of the
configuration files in the system:
