.SH REMOTE CONTROL
.sp
Remote control of Tizonia is possible on environments that support \fI\%D\-Bus\fP\&. Tizonia implements a subset of the
\fI\%Media Player Remote Interfacing Specification\fP\&. More
specifically a subset of the \fI\%MPRIS D\-Bus Interface Specification (version 2)\fP
.sp
Tizonia ships with a tool called \fBtizonia\-remote\fP\&. This tool provides an easy
way access to the subset of the MPRISv2 commands that are implemented.
.SS CONFIGURATION
.sp
The Tizonia configuration file contains a block like this one (see
tizonia\-config\-label) under the \fB[tizonia]\fP section.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
# MPRIS v2 interface enable/disable switch
# \-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-
# Valid values are: true | false
#
mpris\-enabled = false
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \fBmpris\-enabled\fP
Set to \fBtrue\fP or \fBfalse\fP to enable or disable the MPRISv2 remote control
interface. When this element is set to \fBtrue\fP, \fBtizonia\-remote\fP will be
able to control a running instance of Tizonia.
